error[8-0084]: memory-backed contract fields are not supported
    ┌─ immutable_contract_field_init.fe:200:10
    │
200 │     ptr: std::evm::MemPtr<u256>
    │          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ `ptr` has a memory-backed contract field type
    │
    = memory handles cannot be persisted as contract fields; use a plain immutable field for code-backed data or a plain `mut` field for storage-backed state

error[8-0086]: immutable contract field is not initialized
  ┌─ immutable_contract_field_init.fe:2:5
  │
2 │     x: u256
  │     ^ `x` must be assigned in `init` on every successful path
  │
  = assign `x` in `init` with `uses (mut x)`, or mark the field `mut` to store it in contract storage

